##<a id='prereqs'></a> Prerequisites

<!-- If the MariaDB issue has not been fixed, add a note under the VMware Tanzu SQL with MySQL for VMs or external MySQL credentials header about the issue. See 1.2 for example. -->

You must have the following to install <%= vars.product_short %>:

+ <%= vars.app_runtime_full %>  (<%= vars.app_runtime_abbr %>) v2.3.x or later
+ VMware Tanzu SQL with MySQL for VMs (Tanzu SQL for VMs) v2.0 and later or credentials for an existing external MySQL database v5.7 or later.
  + If you are using Tanzu SQL for VMs, you must configure a single node service plan.
  + If binary logging is enabled, the user must have `SUPER` privileges or the global variable `log_bin_trust_function_creators` must be set to `1`.
+ If you want notifications sent to Slack channels, a Slack account
+ If you want notifications sent to email addresses, **Email Configuration** must be enabled and configured on the <%= vars.product_short %> tile

##<a id='install'></a> Download and Install the <%= vars.product_short %> Tile

Follow the procedures below to download and install the <%= vars.product_short %> tile:

1. Download the product file from [<%= vars.product_network %>](https://network.pivotal.io/products/p-event-alerts/).

1. Navigate to the <%= vars.ops_manager %> Installation Dashboard and click **Import a Product** to upload the product file.

1. Under the **Import a Product** button, click **+** next to the version number of <%= vars.product_short %>.
This adds the tile to your staging area.

1. Click the newly added **<%= vars.product_short %>** tile to open its configuration panes.

